article.headline: Wofford 82, Jacksonville St. 80
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Shane Nichols scored 24 points and Drew Gibson added 20 more to help lead Wofford to a 82-80 victory over Jacksonville State on Saturday night. Wofford (3-1) was 83.3 percent from the free throw line with Gibson going 6-for-6 and Nichols completing 7-of-9. Matt O'Connor joined Nichols and Gibson in double digit scoring with 15. It was the home opener for Jacksonville State (0-2), which was led by Courtney Bradley and Dorien Brown. Bradley had a career-high 31 points and 11 rebounds and Brown posted 24 points and 11 rebounds, but it was not enough. Harold Crow rounded out the double digit scoring for the Gamecocks with 11. Jacksonville State trailed by seven with 19 seconds to play, but cut the lead to two by the nine second mark. Nichols made two free throws at eight seconds, but a late dunk by Brown cut the lead back to two. Brown stole an inbound pass from O'Connor and got it to Will Ginn, but his 3-point attempt missed at the buzzer.
